description: An assassins' guild to one side and the Mogura ninja to the other, Usagi Yojimbo is between a rock and a hard place. High in the mountains above ancient Japan, he is forced into battle along the narrow Chrysanthemum Pass. And what is the secret of the medicine peddler?
name: The Chrysanthemum Pass
Angel in Flames, The Conclusion:  A Prayer on Fire

description:
From the visionary minds of writers Grant Morrison and Mark Millar comes a new DC Universe ongoing series with a new kind of hero--one with truly fantastic powers, a limitless sense of wonder, and a refreshing nobility of heart that will fire your imagination and renew your love of comics. Readers weary of psychotic vigilantes and angst-driven executioner "heroes" will find Aztek an invigorating change of pace--a fast-moving, action-packed, intelligent adventure that will challenge your preconceptions and delight you, month after month.

The issue opens in Vanity City, where Piper, a small-time super-villain, engages in a clandestine meeting. Worried about his daughter, Piper is forced to meet with her kidnappers and Synth, a former member of a super-hero team known as the Vat-Men. Synth’s mind is in constant flux, and it is Synth that is “guarding” Piper’ daughter.

Meanwhile, the new hero, Aztek, has arrived in Vanity City. His mission is to get the lay of the land, and to create a secret identity for himself. However, he has no idea how to do that. With no social security number and no money, Aztek has a hard time finding a place to live. He goes to a local bank, trying to figure out a way to get money, when the bank I robbed by Piper and his army of small self-functioning pipes.

Before anyone can do anything, Vanity City’ hero, the ruthless gun-toting Bloodtype arrives on the scene. Bloodtype drops Piper with a couple of fists to the face, and is about to shoot him in the head when Aztek interrupts him. While Bloodtype thinks Aztek is a super-villain, Aztek makes it clear that he is only here to make sure Bloodtype does not go over the top with Piper. Piper tries to run, and Bloodtype guns him down before Aztek can stop him.

Bloodtype finds Aztek is much more capable than Piper, and the two fight. Bloodtype pulls out every weapon he has in his arsenal, but none of them stop Aztek. Aztek uses an electrical jolt to fryBloodtype’s synapses, knocking him unconscious. Aztek approaches Piper, who is barely alive. Piper tells Aztek his real name, Dr. Curt Falconer, and that he was doing this to save his daughter Mindy being held hostage. Just as Aztek is trying to make sense of everything, one of Piper’s pipes runs up. Piper says that this pipe is not one of his, and the pipe explodes, destroying the building.

At the local E.R., the survivors of the explosion are being triaged. Bloodtype is barely alive, having lost both his right leg and arm. Aztek arrives at the hospital in normal clothes, and tries to help. While Bloodtype dies on the gurney, Aztek uses his touch to heal one of the victims. When one of the nurses asks what is going on, Aztek states that he is Dr. Curt Falconer, the new doctor here.

With Bloodtype dead, there is no super-hero watching over Vanity City. Aztek decides to take that role, and reports back to his mysterious bosses, who now have nothing to do but wait for the “shadow god” to show his hand.
name: A Town Called Vanity

description: "Legacy" prelude. Batman, Robin, and Nightwing head to the Sudanese desert in search of a cure to the plague in "Twelve Steps to the Heart of Hell." Guest-starring the Huntress, continued in DETECTIVE COMICS (1937-2011) #700.
name: Twelve steps to the heart of hell

description: Talia, daughter of the demonic Ra's al Ghul, is determined to retrieve one of the world's leading scientists, a man who escaped her father's employ. But Batgirl's on the case, and she's out to make sure Talia doesn't succeed.
name: Tears

description:
Alfred reads a letter from Thomas Wayne to Bruce.

Batman must help a former kidnapping victim get confront her nightmares.

Batman stops a gang of thieves who have broken into a mansion.

Batman confronts an abusive father who uses the threat of the Batman as a punishment for young son.

A hitman disguises himself as Santa to murder a family.
In a skyscraper of deathtraps, the Batman finds his skills are put sorely to the test in a battle for survival against the forces of a Gotham crimelord.
name: Citadel

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Cupid and Psyche are in San Francisco. They have adopted new over-the-top hip-hop looks and personas, calling themselves Q and Fly Kee.

Meanwhile, two suburban white kids, Oscar and Herschel, who are also wanna-be gangstas who are going to work with Q, pass by Tim, Leah, and the other models in their van. Leah kisses Tim to make them jealous, and the two kids crash into a billboard of Leah's while they're distracted.

Tim is taken aback as well, and they discuss how much bigger America is than England, and Leah's old prison of a box.

Tim is attracted to Leah, but is thinking more about Molly, and what she's doing. Leah realizes this, and even defends Tim from the other girls, saying that she likes Molly and they need to back off. Her own crush on Tim, however, is equally clear.

Molly, meanwhile, is in faerie, having been brought there after her bet with the Amadan. People have been trying to trick her into being stuck there, but an elf named Selwyn brings her food in the name of Auberon--food that was purchased in the real world, and thus can be eaten without her being stuck in faerie. She is now just waiting for the contest with Amadan.

Herschel and Oscar finally make it to Q's pad, where he has been making special chocolate hollowpoint bullets for his Z70B gun. They tell him and Psyche that they want revenge on the models, and Q is up for it.

Selwyn advises Molly against playing with Amadan, but Molly sees through her disguise, and Selwyn reveals herself to be Auberon. He asks her to be his new fool, taking Amadan's place. He believes that she has a better grasp of the truth of things, and could help the faeries see themselves more truly. If she agrees, she can ask for a favor.

At the models' agency, Cupid breaks in and sprays down everyone with his love bullets, including Tim and Leah.
name: Rites of Passage, Part One: Down With That

description:
Untethered in time, Wally may be doomed to forever wander the timestream.

Part 4 of "Race Against Time" as John Fox, the flash of the 27th Century, and Wally's girl Linda Park race against the menace threatening to destroy the present with a new ice age!
name: Race Against Time Part 4

description:
"Hard-Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation" part 3, continued from GREEN ARROW (1988-1998) #110. Kyle's father asks the Green Lantern for a favor--a favor that will set him against his ally Green Arrow. Continued in GREEN ARROW (1988-1998) #111.

After stopping Hatchet and breaking up the fight between he, Connor, and Kyle, the man who sent him reveals himself to be Aaron Rayner, Kyle's father. Aaron seemed both surprised and happy to see him. He asks the two to do him a favor and convinces Kyle that he wants to set up a communications satellite, but Connor is suspicious of why. Connor tries to explain his suspicions but Kyle didn't want to hear it. As soon the two of them return to earth they part ways.
name: Hard-Traveling Heroes: the Next Generation part 3

story_arc_credits.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

description: "Difficult Beginnings" part 3, the conclusion to Paul Jenkins' latest epic. John Constantine faces a final choice when he confronts the self he banished to hell, and at last defines his sticky relationship with another otherworldly acquaintance.
name: Difficult Beginnings, Part Three: The Darkening of the Light

description: A shocking revelation from Max Mercury's time-twisted past jolts Manchester and threatens every relationship the speedster has--including the one with his teenaged charge, Impulse.
name: Running from the Past

description: It's Liverpool, England, the year is 2012, and Dane is reunited with a friend from issue #1--with deadly results. Meanwhile, in the House of Fun, Ragged Robin and Jim Crow try deactivating magical bobby traps as Mr. Six releases his floating eyes to track down Dane.
name: The Last Temptation Of Jack
Purge, Part 3: To All Our Company

description:
All hell breaks loose at Jesus de Sade's party, where the overindulgent host is getting more excess than even he bargained for. As Jesse and Cassidy rumble with Bob and Freddy, a pistol-packin' Tulip takes on Starr and a phalanx of heavily-armed psychotics in ""Hunters"" part 4 of 4.

De Sade's party ends in chaos; Cassidy and Tulip are captured by Starr, and The Grail makes a grave mistake....
name: Judgment Night (Hunters Part 4)

description:
Nightwing and Robin come to Paris searching for Ra's men in an effort to stop them before his newly engineered plague can be released on the unsuspecting tourists, who will spread it across the globe allying themselves with Henri Ducard they begin there search of the city.

This issue is part 3 in the Legacy storyline.
name: Born With Teeth

description: It's 1939 and the New York World's Fair is in full swing when the butchered bodies of several young men are found around the fairgrounds. The blood scent from these murders filters into the dreams of Wesley Dodds, drawing in the Golden Age Sandman.
name: The Phantom of the Fair: Act I of II
Gently Stealing (Falling Down To Heaven Part Two)

description: Hellion has set her co-workers on fire, and the Spectre tries to stop her. She lashes her chains at him and makes a mark across his chest.
name: Righteous Anger

description:
Starman's search for information behind the Mist turns deadly when he narrowly survives a super-powered assassin's attack and joins forces with the Golden Age Sandman. But Jack may be in over his head.

Adventure finds Jack on his New York visit with Wesley Dodds and Dian Belmont. The Golden-Age Sandman comes out of retirement!
name: Sand and Stars, Part Two

description:
"Losin' It" part 6 is the stunning conclusion to Superboy's mind-bending arc! Has the Teen of Steel finally lost his mind? And has Knockout finally revealed her true colors?

Helping Superboy defeat a volcanic threat to innocent lives might have been taken as Knockout redeeming her debt to society. However, she had to go and murder the villain in charge.
name: Losin' It! Part 6 of 6: Lost & Found

description: 'Trial by Fire,' part 4 of 6. The only man who can stop the Swamp Thing's deadly plans is a determined John Constantine - who must relive the horrors of his past while preparing for his final confrontation with the Earth Elemental. But Abby faces an even tougher task when her daughter, Tefe, returns.
name: Trial by Fire, Part 4: Judas Tree

description: LEVEL comes to its startling conclusion as Wonder Woman, Champion, and the new Wonder Girl band together to bring down the monstrous Doomsday! All this and the Man of Steel, too!
name: Game Over

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
In a cut-throat future where commerce is totally electronic and all information is in computer data form, big companies can corrupt control the people and work outside the law.  
 
Lady Supreme infiltrates the company of a woman named Coffin in Amber City and warns her to clean up her act. Coffin simply laughs at her as only moments before she had a staff member killed for making an investment that failed to make money, even thought it didn't loose money either. 
 
She laments that in her time in this new city she's failed to achieve much at all. She battled Loki with Supreme, who died during the battle, sending Loki back to the mists. 
 
When she comes across a robbery in an alleyway she extremely violently dispatches the robbers. Leaving her concerned that she is losing control. Lost in thought she runs into Glory who is concerned about her state of mind and her violent example to the citizens. Glory tells her that her mother would be ashamed.. which angers the test-tube born Supreme. Glory contradicts her saying that she is her mother.
name: Die & Let Die, Part 2 - A Call to Armageddon

description: Cyan's shoelace is the only physical clue to Terry's mysterious recovery from cancer. Terry's nightmares mirror Al's experiences. Spawn enters Hell's fifth level where he is revered as a returning savior. He is forced into a confrontation with the Savage Dragon and defeats the dragon for the position of the Messiah. The dwellers of Hell turn on both of them and stone them to death - or do they?
name: Messiah

description: The Avengers team-up with the X-Men to take down Onslaught. The teams track down Magneto, believing he is at fault. The team discovers that Magneto is now “Joseph”, a de-aged and amnesiac version of the X-Men’s foe. But why is Rogue fighting the Avengers tooth and nail to protect Joseph? And is this “de-aged Magneto” really the man he claims to be?
name: Sins of the Father

description: In this issue we find out if Captain America lives...or dies.
name: Sanctuary
Onslaught Impact 1: For the Sake of the Children

name: Onslaught Impact, Part 1: Cable Vision
The Secrets of Betty Brant!

name: Arachnamorphosis

name: Onslaught Phase 1: In the Company of Strangers

description:
The Sea-snake finds its latest meal some what unpalatable and sends the team back into the open ocean where Gax has a rather R2D2-like moment. 
 
Alia Rellapor 's secret is revealed to an unimpressed Akiko and Poog helps guide them to safety. 
 
Splukler's devil-may-care attitude makes a discovery that just might give Mr. Beeba a whole new perspective on their situation.

Xena's home Amphilpolis is burned down and her mother taken captive by the army that committed the heinous act. And it looks like the Aesor's, the leader of the army, right-hand man is none other than... Hercules?!

Xena and Gabrielle manage to fight off the army, but Hercules and Aesor run away. One seriously enraged warrior princess rides to the home of the hero, only to discover that he's celebrating his mother's birthday with his friends.

Once Hercules has convinced Xena that he wasn't the one who burned down her hometown, the heroes team up to find out who's really behind the villainous act and who's been impersonating Hercules.
name: The Warrior Princess: Part One of Three

description:
The townspeople's patience begins to wear thin as Phoney continues to press them for his “dragon slayer” fees. He lectures the townsfolk on the dangers of hoarding their goods and announces how he plans to use everything he has collected to lure a dragon and kill it (in actuality, a ruse to flee with all his ill-gotten gains). Meanwhile, Thorn, exhausted and unable to sleep for fear of her dreams, decides to return to the farm house, throwing down her sword and leaving the village.

In the mountains enclosing the valley, the Rat Creature army and the Pawans have massed under the instructions of The Hooded One. They are, just as Lucius and Gran'ma Ben feared, preparing to strike at the inhabitants of the valley.
name: The Midsummer Day's Plan

description:
Apocalypse awakens and consults the Watcher. And Onslaught gathers his minions!

The Avengers help the X-Men with a plan on how to defeat Onslaught!
name: [untitled]

description:
Aquaman goes to Tritonis to enlist their aid, but Kordax and the Poseidonians have already beaten them there!

The alien race "The Explorers' have visited the white house in order to gain support following their failure with the oceans sea population.While back in the ocean Aquaman return to learn that Tritonis has been destroyed,with the people being captured by Kordax controlled Atlanteans. Atlan then begins reaching out to Arion calling for his aid.The three then enter the Tritonian ruins where they confront Kordax, Vulko and Koryak , with a wager being made of Garth fighting Koryak for the fate of Lady S'ONA and Aquaman's life which Garth casually wins. Aquaman and Kordax then enter into a telepathic battle for the Atlanteans, causing pain with all beings of the sea with Aquaman having to stop to save all of their lives.

Aquaman then gathers Atlan, Arion, The Guardian of Hy-Basil, Garth, Tsunami, Nuada Dolphin, Power Girl, The Sea Devils and Deep Blue to battle the Hunters.
name: Deep Trouble

description:
The Cable/Onslaught crossover issue! Far into the future, Cable fights an uphill battle to save the X-Men of the past. But how is the Hulk involved in this saga? And will he and Cable be able to cooperate long enough to stop Onslaught together?

Cable is weakened from his battle with Post but the trouble is just beginning because here comes a mind-controlled Hulk. Cable tries to calm Hulk down and Hulk reverts from his mindless Hulk to the smart Hulk. Cable realizes this is a trick when he notices Hulk is telepathically blocked form him. Hulk punts Cable across the landscape but manages to use his telekinesis to slam the Hulk through the ground.

To Cable's surprise, Hulk emerges from the rubble in his grey form and starts to pummel Cable. Cable still tries to convince Hulk that he is being controlled but Hulk doesn't like Cable in his head and smashes him with a diner. Storm arrives just in time to save Cable from certain death by lifting the diner off of him with her wind powers.

Cable is unconscious and his Techno-Virus is spreading rapidly. His heart has stopped. Storm gives him CPR and uses lightning to restart Cable's heart. Hulk returns to the battle and Cable mentally guides Storm's power to send a bolt of lightning into Hulk's brain and hits him with a telepathic bullet. This causes Hulk to turn back green, unfortunately for them though he turns into the Savage Hulk.

In the end, Ozymandias is greeted by Apocalypse who knows that now is the time to begin his preparations.
name: Onslaught Phase 1: Loose Cannons

description: The men and women of the Gotham City Police Department deal with the day-to-day crime of one of the most dangerous cities in the DC Universe. Renee Montoya and Mackenzie Bock foil a terrorist attack, Harvey Bullock and his new partner Kevin Soong investigate a serial killer, and Stan Kitch and Caz Salluci question a lawyer working as a fence for a ring of burglars.
name: Model Citizens

description: The villain Bloodwraith is back and claiming lives for his evil sword. For example, he steals the life of a suicidal construction worker.
name: Possessed by Proctor's Sword

description:
Overview
Star Wars, Nexus, and Ghost -- three all-new stories in one great comic! Dark Horse continues its tenth-anniversary celebration in the second issue of A Decade of Dark Horse, featuring Jabba the Hutt's first meeting with Salacious Crumb; Ursula's not-so-subtle mind games with Nexus; and a startling physical transformation for Ghost! Such an incredible line-up of stories by such an incredible line-up of writers and artists! Who could not celebrate?!

name: Le nuvole negli occhi

description: Luse fights his kidnappers...
name: Three: Death

description: Someone kills Undertow, a former member of Stormwatch, and Weatherman One is determined to find his killer. He sends Fahrenheit, Hellstrike and Jack Hawksmoor to investigate the crime. Meanwhile, Battalion is Stormwatch's new training leader and tests Jenny Sparks for her battle prowess. Fahrenheit learns that it was the American government that killed Undertow, as a show of retaliation against the United Nation's world government. Henry Bendix informs the President that he is aware of the retaliation.
This wiki page is a stub. Hit the edit button above to add to this article.
name: Out of the Blue
Lost Souls, Part 1 - Little Girls Lost

description: Lois helps S.T.A.R. Labs capture Parasite, without Superman's help.
name: Suckered In!

description:
The Emerald Empress becomes the team's greatest threat yet as one Legionnaire pays a terrible price in a futile attempt to save a friend.

The Legionnaires continue to team-up with the Workforce to help Leland McCauley defeat Dr. Regulus and save his industrial site. Dr. Regulus heat-based vision allows him greater mobility on the polluted world, overwhelming several squads and forcing one Legionnaire to make an ultimate sacrifice to stop Regulus before anyone else can get hurt. That sacrifice pushes Shrinking Violet over the edge, bursting with suspicious emerald energy and transporting the group back to Earth.
name: Evil Eye!

description:
Overview

Tarzan has many friends among the creatures of the jungle, but few are as close to him as the mighty lion Jad-bal-ja. He is an honorable beast, and would protect Tarzan at any cost. But infected with the Tara virus, he is Tarzan's most fearsome enemy!

Stormwatch Black is called in to investigate claims about the police department in the city of Lincoln that may be sporting super-powered officers that are inclined to police brutality. Stormwatch is able to defeat them and apprehend the super-powered officers, sending them to cryogenic stasis.
Released divided as a 3 part story in 13A 13B and 13C.

Mad Hettie, Lady Johanna Constantine, three untrustworthy fairies, and an idealistic young British architect named Brian converge on a certain forest on midsummer night's eve...in different centuries.
name: The Lost Boy, Part One

description: The Man of Muscle Mystery survives his passage through the transporter tube, a baptism of blood that places him in the secret base of the Legion of Legions, there to meet the leader of Faculty X. And out of the endless chaos, the Singer's consciousness returns, where he finds himself in the most unexpected place.
name: After the 'Fact', Part Four: We Are All UFOs

description:
A new vigilante is prowling the streets of Gotham City. He's Nightfist, and he's a man with a price on his head that Hitman means to collect. But Nightfist isn't exactly the hero he pretends to be, and while Tommy Monaghan goes on the hunt for him, the infamous Johnny Navarone is closing in to win the bounty for executing Hitman.

Gotham City's newest urban vigilante is just a degenerate drug dealer.
name: Ten Thousand Bullets, Part 2

description: How the Saint met his wife, and lost her; he goes back to Ratwater, looking for revenge and nearly gets it.
name: Saint of Killers Part 2

description: B.B. gets a room at the Herculean Arms and discovers something hidden in the ceiling, while the origin of the infamous Crown Jewels of Alcazar is revealed. And as Charity faces certain doom in the evil clutches of L'il Big Lil, Cosmo dons his human fly gear for the first time in years and comes to the rescue
name: Episode Three

description: Hellboy thought this assignment was over when he bagged the vampire, Giurescu. Well, think again! Giurescu's mistress is Hecate, an ancient spirit of chaos, and she's not going to let her man go without a fight! It's the world's greatest paranormal investigator against chaos incarnate in Hellboy: Wake the Devil, the most disastrous mission in the history of the Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense! And in the penultimate chapter of "Silent as the Grave," Gary Gianni's MonsterMen reveal the ghostly hand behind a series of deaths going back eighty years.
name: Chapter Four

description: OverviewThe Tara virus has killed many men and many beasts, and now it threatens Tarzan's most beloved friend, Jane. It may be Tarzan's most fearsome foe yet -- a foe he cannot battle -- and that it was brought to earth by the Lord of the Jungle himself only makes Tarzan's fury that much greater.

name: Angel in Hiding, Part One: Renunciation

description:
The excitement continues for Aztek, the newest hero of the DC Universe, as Green Lantern guest-stars! Everyone in Vanity is wondering about the city's mysterious new adventurer, Aztek, especially the underworld bosses who run the city. Anxious to nip this troublesome hero in the bud, the gangs deploy their own metahuman to deal with Aztek. And if that wasn't enough, Major Force hits town, demanding a piece of the action.

With Bloodtype dead, criminals try to rob one of Vanity City’s banks. They are stopped by Major Force, who kills three of the four robbers. He leaves a message for the fourth to carry to the Vanity City underworld: he wants in. The crime bosses call in Synth to arrange a meeting, after Synth is to dispose of Mindy Falconer.

At St. Batholomew’s Hospital, Aztek is trying to adjust to his role as Dr. Curt Falconer. While there, he neatly avoids supervisor Julia Frostick while unknowingly making a date with nurse Joy Page. Aztek takes to the skies, continuing his search for college student Mindy Falconer.

Meanwhile, the appearance of Major Force in Vanity City draws Green Lantern Kyle Rayner. Rayner is still after Major Force after the major killed Rayner’s girlfriend Alexandra DeWitt. Rayner meets with the Vanity City P.D., who believes Major Force to be dead. Rayner decides to continue to investigate, and heads off to find either Major Force, or Vanity City’s newest hero Aztek.

Rayner finds Aztek, and encases him in a plasma bubble. Aztek escapes the bubble, and somehow manages to take Rayner’s power ring. Aztek offers it back if they could act as friends, not enemies. Rayner agrees, and gets his ring back. Aztek asks Rayner to come with him to help find Mindy Falconer.

They find Mindy Falconer, but she is now allies with Major Force. Aztek and Rayner continue to spy, and find out that Major Force is not actually Major Force, but rather a shape-changing Synth. Synth and Mindy have decided to take over the Vanity City criminal underworld, and have set up this ambush. We find out Synth had the ability to be either super-intelligent or super-idiotic every other day.

Aztek, Rayner, and the Vanity City P.D. break in, and subdue the villains. During the fight, Synth’s super-IQ turns off, and he accidentally shoots Mindy Falconer through the heart. Aztek and Green Lantern part as friends, and the Vanity Press name their new super-hero Aztek.
name: Too Many Crooks

description:
Batman is in Calcutta trying to foil Ra's al Ghul's plan to infect the poverty-stricken city with a deadly plague. Batman's thoughts inform us that even though Calcutta is a city of squalor, the people who live there are inspiring. Batman vows that the city will be saved.

Racing along the rooftops, he receives a call from Oracle. Oracle tells him to go the the temple of Kali to meet his contact who will have more information. She is wary to say too much, in case Ra's people are listening.

Batman jumps down into an alleyway, where a local boy watches him in wonder. The street urchin asks him if he's English or American. Batman tells him that he's American, and he wants to be left alone. The child asks him if he's wearing his costume for the upcoming Festival of Durga. Batman tells him no; he's dressed that way to save the world and tells the boy to go home. The boy informs Bats that he lives in the alley, and therefore IS home. Batman warns him that if he stays he could be in great danger. Eventually, the boy retreats into the shadows.

Batman looks around for his contact, who turns out to be Lady Shiva. Lady Shiva is proud to see that Bruce has reclaimed his position as Batman, and wonders if she had helped if Azrael was still wearing the cowl. Unbeknownst to the two, the boy watches them from the shadows. Shiva tells the Dark Knight that Ra's al Ghul's agents plan to meet on the bridge crossing the Hooghly River. Batman deduces that they must be planning to introduce the virus into the city's water supply.

They walk forward a bit, and Lady Shiva reveals that she was being followed. What's more is she knew she was being followed, but she wanted to lead them into a trap. The urchin watches in amazement from his hiding place, as the two easily defeat the murderous thugs. Batman takes the ring from a fallen man's finger. Shiva points out that is unlike him, but Bats tells her that it isn't for him, either. They stop at a food stand, where Bruce gives the ring to the proprietor and tells him to feed the child.

Batman and Lady Shiva arrive at the bridge, only to discover that is where the Festival of Durga is occurring. The river is full of adherents and statues. Shiva tells him that each year, the celebrants dump the clay statues into the river; where they melt on their way to the sea. The boy shows up, and grabs Batman's cape. Batman reminds the boy that he warned him to stay away, as Shiva points out several assassins in the crowd. The assassins rush to the bridge, but Batman and Shiva chase after them and begin fighting. One of the thugs pulls a gun and is about to fire, when the urchin jumps on him from behind. The assassin easily knocks the boy back and shoots him coldly. This enrages Batman, who knocks the thug down and breaks his arm. He asks the thug about the virus. The thug tells him that the virus is hidden in one of the statues that has been thrown into the water. He then commits suicide by biting down on a poison tooth.

Without a thought, Batman jumps into the river and searches for the virus-filled statue. He finally sees a green mass floating up and manages to capture it; the virus container is still intact and Calcutta is safe. Back on the riverbank, Batman picks up the child who is still alive, though gravely injured. He picks the boy up in his arms and walks away, as Lady Shiva looks on.
name: A Wound on the Heart of Heaven

description: Batman must travel to Ra's al Ghul's island to stop the villain's plans for spreading a deadly disease to the rest of the world.
name: Blood of the Demon

description:
A seemingly normal, harmless and innocent guy decides he'll do one very bad thing in his entire life.The plot? To kill The Batman.

Batman battles a mad scientist who is performing horrible experiments on people.

Batman rescues an inventor and his young son from the Nazis during World War II.

A critically wounded Batman has visions of the people he knows leaving him.

Batman is taunted by a serial killer with multiple personalities.

name: Conspiracy Part 1 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Having shot Tim and Leah with his love bullets, Cupid--who has reimagined himself as a wanna-be-gangsta--threatens to shoot the rest of the models and make them fall in love with unsuitable suitors unless the owner of the agency pays up.

Tim uses his magic to cover Cupid in wrapping paper. Cupid confesses to his problems, complaining that Valentines' Day cards have made him meaningless and cheesy. He wanted to prove that he could still make anyone love each other.

However, Tim and Leah laugh off his chocolate bullets, which had no effect. Leah, the succubus, tells Cupid what love is really like.

Molly, who has taken on Auberon's job as his fool, wanders the area around the castle, finding examples of fairies who come up with absurd magical explanations for everyday occurrences. For instance, a groom says his horse has been cursed so his mane and tail will always be tangled, and he will always limp, but it's really because he has a stone in his hoof and he doesn't brush him.

Leah just pops the stone out of his hoof. But, she takes a special interest in him because she can tell he hasn't always been a horse.

Tim is ready to leave the modeling agency, but Psyche, who has taken to her new gangsta role more seriously than Cupid, pulls a real gun on Leah. She demands money. Tim doesn't know what to do, since she'll be able shoot before he makes a magical gesture.

He decides to provoke her, ridiculing her "fly girl" thing. She hits him, which gives him time to release his butterfly tattoo, returning her to her previous state (in which she had butterfly wings), where she is no longer angry.

The lady Titania sits in Faerie, pondering the current state Auberon is in, which is mysterious to her. He seems more questioning and passionate. Unknown to her, he is there, disguised again as Selwyn.

They hear Molly, building a tree house. She is bored with being bored, and wants to actually do something, create something--activities that fairies have forgotten about. After first making fun of her, the Queen's fairies see the fun, and join in with Molly in building the tree house.

The Queen is not amused, and begins to plan an ultimate curse for Molly.
name: Rites of Passage, Part Two: This Is Not About Chocolate

description:
The Flash must once again risk contact with the Speed Force in order to return to his home time and save Keystone City from another ice age.

Flash's "Race Against Time" concludes! Can Wally make it back from the future through the Speed Force in time to save Linda and all of Keystone City from another ice age? And what, at last, has John Fox been up to all this time?
name: Race Against Time Part 5

description:
All of Manhattan seems to be coming down around Green Lantern just when he has an appointment he has to keep--a date with Donna Troy.

Kyle is late for an appointment but he can't seem to get there to see the mystery woman how is wanting for him. He stops a run away train, saves a small boy from a burning building, stops an armed robbery and even rescues a cat from a tree, all the while the mystery woman waits. After a quick visit to John Stewart who is still in the hospital recovering from his battle with Grayven, Kyle recharges his ring and meets the mystery woman, Donna Troy.

The two old lovers have a long walk on the beach and discuss where there relationship went wrong. Kyle uses his ring to make Donna a necklace and promises as long as he believes in them the necklace will be solid. The last scene is the two in a kissing embrace.
name: A Beginning

description: Time and space twist and collide when John Constantine experiences a weird sense of deja vu while on a case--one that traces back to the 19th Century and James Constantine of Porlock!
name: A Taste of Heaven

description: Bart sticks his nose into Zatanna's magic show and causes some simple sleight-of-hand to go horribly awry, depositing Impulse and Zatanna in a mystic land with deadly danger for both of them!
name: Quicker than the Eye

description: "House of Fun" part 3 of 3! Boy and Mr. Six swim through the malignant debris of an exploding abscess while Dane faces the diabolical King-of-All-Tears.
name: Good-Bye Baby Rabbits

description:
In this epilogue to ""Hunters,"" the Grail thinks Cassidy is Jesse Custer...and their Messiah, to boot! Captured by Starr and his henchmen, Cassidy continues his masquerade and discovers new secrets about the clandestine order.

Starr takes Cassidy to Masada, the headquarters of The Grail - and The Grail's ancient plan is revealed, as is Cassidy's identity; Jesse and Tulip find out where Cassidy is and make plans to rescue him.
name: Miracle Man (Hunters Epilogue)

description: As the aftermath of Bane and Batman's battle picks up with Batman trying to save the defeated villain, as Robin, Huntress and Nightwing sneak aboard Ra's boat in order to infiltrate his computer databases.With the three heroes having defeated Ra's and Talia the issue comes to a close with several bodies floating in from the neighboring city of Bluhaven.
name: Riptide

description: Wesley Dodds's dreams are besieged by images of brutal crimes plaguing the 1939 New York City World's Fair. Thus, the Fair becomes the hunting ground of the Golden Age Sandman--and a cop named Jim Corrigan, who will one day become the Spectre! "Phantom of the World's Fair" part 2.
name: The Phantom of the Fair: Act II of II
What You Need (Falling Down To Heaven Part Three)

description: A group of men beats up a gay couple in an alley, killing one of them. The Spectre intervenes and rips out the heart of the attacker who struck the fatal blow.
name: Acts of God

description:
Jack Knight has been captured! As the conflict unfolds and the clock ticks away, the Golden Age Sandman must call on the memory of his first battle alongside the original Starman to save the day in a sequence illustrated by Guy Davis (SANDMAN MYSTERY THEATRE)!

When Jack goes missing, Wesley recalls a previous time he encountered a Starman. The Gambler had kidnapped Ted Knight, The Golden-Age Starman. Dodds stepped in to rescue his colleague, and friend. It may be time for his to step in again.
name: Sand and Stars, Part Three

description: In the aftermath of the startling revelations of last issue's events, Superboy attempts to get some much needed R&R. But when a shape-changing surfer and the beautiful bounty-hunter from outer space that is hunting him show up, the Teen of Steel does not have long to relax.
name: ... Wipeout!

description: 'Trial by Fire,' part 5 of 6. Swamp Thing's final trial awaits him far from Earth, courtesy of the Parliament of Flames. But first, stripped of his elemental abilities, he must survive the murderous attack of The Word. And just what is John Constantine up to now?
name: Trial by Fire, Part 5: Apocalypse Now

description: The new Wonder Girl, Cassandra Sandsmark, sets out to make her mark on the world, but her first time out may be her, as she comes face-to-face with Decay!
name: Are You Out of Your Minds

description: Al Simmons is returned to his demonic birthplace where he is attacked by Billy Kincaid, after beheading him he is tormented by a legion of demons in the likeness of Wanda. When he realizes that Malebolgia has tricked him, he destroys the demons and passes another of the Malebolgia's tests. Malebolgia then agrees to leave Wanda alone in exchange for Al's loyalty and servitude. Spawn then enters Terry's dreams where he suddenly awakens knowing that Al is "alive."
name: The Reckoning
